This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new method for training ensembles of models that improve generalization and diversity. The paper also mentions tasks related to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are closely related to machine learning. Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of covariate shift, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper introduces a new diversity metric, which is related to data analysis and statistics (cs.DS).
